Afrofusionist, TÖME enlists Nigerian neo-alternative artiste, Wavy the Creator on her latest offering, “Magical Fruits.” The lofi-esque record finds the two trading endearing words about their fantasies and other things, concealed. TÖME is a Canada-resident Nigerian Afrofusion artiste. She spent most of 2019 touring Europe with Mr Eazi and shared the stage at Burna Boy’s iconic Wembley Arena concert in London. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-1151121 size-full lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Magical-Fruits-Artwork-1-e1588325634337.jpg" alt="" width="1280" height="1280" /> Magical Fruits is the second single from TÖME’s soon-to-come sophomore album; Bigger than 4 Walls slated for a May 22 release. Listen here Listen: Megan Thee Stallion Features Beyonce In “She Can Be All”